pageContext.description: "Hollow ring of nearly circular section, but slightly flattened on one face. Through the periphery are three broad openings almost touching each other so that the supports from one face of the ring to the other are at three of the corners of a square. The fourth side of the square is a smaller opening." (Archaeologia).
pageContext.patina: Dull black patina with a green tinge.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,Purchased by the Cambridge Antiquarian Society, April 1919,1919.6
pageContext.site: England,Cambridgeshire,Wilburton,In fen-land belonging to Mr. Oliver Claude Pell.,1882
